***ATTENTION PARENTS/GUARDIANS***
We were just notified that federal waivers from the USDA have been approved to allow us to feed students meals free of charge as long as funding exists. This will include breakfast and lunch. All Texhoma students 5-12th grades will be able to eat breakfast and lunch free of charge beginning September 1st. Anything prior to September 1st will require payment, statements will be sent out next week. We are excited to be able to offer this service to our students!

post_text: Weren't able to attend graduation, or for some reason you missed it? No worries, because we are going to re-air the graduation here on Facebook Tuesday, May 19th at 7:00 P.M. We again would like to thank everyone who made graduation possible this year. One important production note; The songs from the senior video as well as the rose ceremony have been removed to protect ourselves from any possible copyright issues. Feel free to search the songs (5 More Minutes, My Wish, I'll Be There For You, and I Got a Feeling) and blare them on your own speakers for the full experience or even try out your own songs to play along with our slides. Do check out Christina Gideon's song though doing this presentation. MULTIPLE times I have had members of other communities come ask me for the name of the Youtube star we got to sing that song for us, not realizing that it was one of our own extremely talented seniors.

post_text:
Hello from Coach T!

Testive is offering free online proctored practice SATs/ACTs tests every Wednesday and Saturday through the summer.

Testive's weekly online practice tests emulate the experience of an official SAT or ACT to give students an incredibly productive prep experience. The online tests are supported by a Testive Student Advisor, run a full 3 hours (just like the real exams) and can be done from the comfort and safety of home. And scores are given immediately after the test is completed.

Parents can register via this link: https://www.testive.com/free-practice-test/



Please see the attached flyer for more information about the practice tests. Testive is a partner of XAP, the vendor that powers OKcollegestart.

post_text:
Family and Friends of the Texhoma Graduating Class of 2020: We understand that many of you are having to make concessions in order to create this memorable event for your child. We at Texhoma appreciate your understanding that the guidelines we must adhere to are in place for the safety of everyone attending the graduation. We must also honor the owners of the Drive In, the volunteers at KKBS and the staff at Texhoma by adhering to these guidelines.
1. Please do not enter the park before 8PM
2. No one can exit their vehicle once you enter the park
3. Pickup beds cannot have people in them
4. The only person to exit any vehicle will be the graduate and one family member from his/her car to take pictures.

text:
Family and Friends of the Texhoma Graduating Class of 2020: We understand that many of you are having to make concessions in order to create this memorable event for your child. We at Texhoma appreciate your understanding that the guidelines we must adhere to are in place for the safety of everyone attending the graduation. We must also honor the owners of the Drive In, the volunteers at KKBS and the staff at Texhoma by adhering to these guidelines.
1. Please do not enter the park before 8PM
2. No one can exit their vehicle once you enter the park
3. Pickup beds cannot have people in them
4. The only person to exit any vehicle will be the graduate and one family member from his/her car to take pictures.
5. There will be no access to restrooms

Ty McBride
April 23 at 8:56 AM ·

I don't know what it is, but checking my students work 3 weeks into distance learning and seeing that I'm only missing work from 14 of my 80 students with 2 days still left in the week makes me super proud of students. Distance learning requires self discipline and self determination that only grows more difficult with every week, and yet 82% of my students are not only rising to the occasion, but they are doing it with spectacular timing that you wouldn't even see in majority of successful adults.

Beginning Friday, April 10 Texhoma Schools will be joining schools across the nation by turning on the stadium lights on Friday nights at 8:20, which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them on for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. We invite the Texhoma Corona Cruise to swing by around 8:20 and honk as the lights come on in honor of our 2020 Senior Graduates!

During the week the lights will be on for one hour as a beacon of hope that together we will overcome the pandemic and soon return to normal routines with a greater appreciation of all the things and people we are blessed with in our lives.

post_text: The Oklahoma State Board of Education met today at 4:00. The Board voted in favor of mandatory closure of all Oklahoma public schools from March 17 through April 6. Texhoma Schools will be closed as per this mandate. Our administrative staff is working closely with the Texas side administrative staff as best we can as we are all on spring break and out of town. We will be monitoring the situation and getting information out to you as soon as decisions are made. We ask you to please be patient as we are all dealing with a situation we have never dealt with before. Our main concern is the health and safety of our students, staff and community. Please share this message to our community so that parents and teachers know about the mandated extended break. Continue to check back on Facebook and our website for updated information.

March 2 at 5:21 PM ·

There is so much power in a number. 10! To some this number may be small, but to me it means everything. This year I have 20 students in speech. 10 out of 20 will compete at regionals in less than 4 weeks. That is 50% of the class. This is the biggest group I have taken. We may be small, but we are growing. If you all happen to see
Andrea Zavala
Olivia Turcios
Dominic Royse
Eli Ortega
Olivia Merry
Wyatt Merry
Jarrett Burrow
Gage Thrasher
Cody Burke
Erick Sanchez
Please congratulate them. It is very difficult to get up in front of a crowd and give a speech. I am extremely proud of this group, and I know we will represent at state. I want to thank my amazing hubby Ty McBride and Connie Miller for being my rocks, supporters, and encouragers. It's a great day to be a Red Devil!

shared_text:
Season McBride is with Nathan McAuliffe and 10 others.
February 29 at 5:11 PM ·

Dale Carnegie said, “There are always three speeches, for every one you actually gave. The one you practiced, the one you gave, and the one you wish you gave.” The only people who will wholeheartedly understand this quote are the people have had to give a speech. I am proud to say that 20 students from Texhoma High School understand this quote completely. My speech team has come such a long way since August. Some have accomplished something that they never imagined that they would. Speech is terrifying and exciting all at the same time. I am so proud of my team. Even though we only had two people qualify for regionals today, each student accomplished something huge! Congrats to Jarrett Burrow and Olivia Turcios for receiving 2nd place in Humorous Duet. I'm so proud of all of my kids. #regionalsbound #4weekstogo

We are currently unable to show the 2020 Miss Texhoma Pageant in it's entirely on Facebook; However we will keep the video of the crowning on the page for your viewing. A Google folder has been made with the video files from the entire pageant for your personal viewing. You may share the link and file to your family and friends, but we do ask that you do not try to publish the videos on any social networking sites like Facebook and Youtube. The link is located at the bottom of this post.

post_text: Our local hero!
shared_text:
Oklahoma State Department of Education
January 28 at 4:19 PM ·

Take a look at Jackson Schroeder, a freshman at Texhoma High School and one of only 16 USA parapalegic high school students selected to represent America in the International Wheelchair and Amputee Sports Federation (a pre-paralympics competition) hosted in Thailand this year!

You inspire us, Jackson! And bravo to Texhoma Public Schools for supporting and celebrating this talented young man.

"It's like you're representing this town, our program, everything...'cause when you win, Texhoma wins, we win, everybody wins."

We are so proud of our 2019-2020 Red Devil football team and coaches. It's always a great day to be a Red Devil!
